Hope you enjoy the video. We're on our way to Arizona now. 

💜 @deservingdogs

and I'd be lying if I said I was completely okay going into next week. Every night I just cuddle with Freddie and she gets so excited about it. I have moments of laughter but it can suddenly turn into me crying and scared at the possibilities of putting Freddie through surgery on Thursday. I have no choice though. Her teeth are infected and they must come out. 

I just want to share this moment with you and express my truth this week. I'm scared. Please everyone start praying, meditating, light a candle, do whatever you do to send strong vibes to Freddie that her surgery goes great on October 29th. I need support right now and I know she has so many others who love her too. 

Thank you all.

@deservingdogs

node.text: Freddie lost the last of her bottom teeth yesterday. Her lower jaw has completely disappeared. I expected this but worried about how it would effect her eating. So far we have adapted and she's doing well. I can't even believe the changes in her mouth until I look at an old photo. This first photo is of her two years ago and the last photo I took of her yesterday. Now she just has cute little fangs.

This is my crazy baby brother Buggy. 😂

Buggy is a 9 month old pug who became paralyzed when his human children accidently dropped something on him fracturing his spinal cord. They didn't know how to care for him and said he was too much work so that's how we ended up with him. As soon as I get him I knew he would stay forever. 🙈 

He's the most hilarious little dog and so full of energy and joy everyday. He's even starting to walk on his own thanks to @atlasrehab4canines. 

I hope this video makes you laugh and brightens your day today!

node.text: Sometimes she likes to try and eat on her own and then she'll give me a look like she's ready for me to help her. Freddie's bottom jaw is now almost completely gone and the last tooth that remains is super loose so I imagine she's going to lose it soon. We've figured out her feedings well though. It has to be the right food (@luckydogcuisine), the right consistency for me to be able to put it in her mouth (not too watery) and she always likes to start by trying to eat first followed by me hand feeding her. She's never gained more weight in her life before so she's doing the best she ever has. 💙🙏

node.text:
I'd like to take a moment to express my gratitude to each and every one of you. A week ago I posted about us losing our housing abruptly and you guys sprang into action to help us. 

We put a link in our bio that a follower set up for us and within a couple of days it raised over $30,000! 🤯🎉 

I'm thrilled, grateful, excited and can not wait to put that all to good use! All together the GoFundMe has raised over $90k and I just really don't have words to even convey how thankful I am to all of you guys. Every dollar we got is going towards us buying a house and getting into a permanent spot where we can continue to be a foster and safe place for the Freddies of the world. 

My passion is helping paralyzed dogs, dogs with special medical needs and dogs that others just simply can not care for because of the amount of work they are. I have dedicated my life to this and I will continue to do so for years to come. I volunteer all my time caring for large groups of dogs who have many needs both physically and mentally and it fulfills me on levels I never thought possible. 

I will be forever grateful to all of you who have showed love and support during this challenging time. 

Freddie is in the best shape of her life right now and thriving and I can't wait for the day when I'm giving her a tour of her permanent home. The home we will continue to heal so many animals thanks to all of you.

Eternally grateful. Can't wait to share more of this journey with all of you. I love you all.

node.text:
We need your help! 🆘

Today we were given a 30 day eviction notice from our rental. The building we live in went up for sale two weeks ago and the new owner isn't okay with us living here with animals. Obviously I would never give up any of the dogs I care for so I have 30 days to figure out a solution. 

I've had to move every single year for the last ten years of my life and I really want stability for all of the dogs I care for and the fosters I take in. They need a safe place. 

A GoFundMe was started by one of our followers and has already reached over $60k. We're going to use this money to purchase a permanent residence so I never have to go through this with all the dogs again. If you can help, even a dollar I would appreciate it so much. 

If you can't help but feel like sharing this post I would be so grateful. 

I don't know where I can go, even temporarily with all of my animals. I currently have 5 dogs of my own and 6 foster dogs and 4 foster cats. I've been working hard on getting some of them adopted into their forever homes but some need more time with me for rehabilitation so I need to find a temp spot for all of us to be together. 

I'm in a bit of a panic mode right now and not really sure what my next steps are but felt the need to get my situation out there. 

Thank you all for reading this far and for any support you can offer right now. I need it. My animals need it. Thank you.
